# dns_overrides.yaml — MAC address -> DNS label
#
# Copy this file to dns_overrides.yaml (or any path you like), point the
# DNS_OVERRIDES_FILE env var at it, and the dashboard will use these
# labels in place of whatever name the FRITZ!Box reports for each device.
#
# Useful for devices whose Fritzbox name is junk like "ESP_4F3A21" or
# generic like "iPhone" — pin them to a stable, sensible label here.
#
# - Top level is a flat mapping. No nesting.
# - Keys are MAC addresses. Quote them — YAML's bare-scalar rules around
#   colons get fiddly otherwise.
# - Casing in the YAML doesn't matter; the loader uppercases keys to
#   match what the FRITZ!Box returns.
# - Labels follow RFC 1035: letters, digits, hyphens. They're not
#   re-sanitized, so type them the way you want them in DNS.

"AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF": kitchen-sensor
"11:22:33:44:55:66": hallway-pi
"DE:AD:BE:EF:00:01": living-room-tv
